<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FCDFE4348A7547AFE2BFAEE" pageId="387" pageNumber="388" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FCDFE4348A7547AFEBCFB0A" blockId="387.[150,1437,854,1598]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FCDFE4348A7547AFE0CFC9F" bold="true" box="[151,425,854,879]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 2.5–3.0 mm. Testaceous-yellow, except petiole black and occasionally metasoma brownish. Antenna clavate. Antennal segments in following proportions: 8:5:11:6.5:5:4:5 (segments 8–10 missing in 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCDFE43496D54B2FE64FC46" box="[349,449,926,950]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">holotype</typeStatus>
). Head excavated, shiny, smooth, hairless, unsculptured, except occiput and anterior region of face granulated. Palpal formula 6/3. Pronotum shiny, unsculptured, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum shiny, unsculptured, without lateral pointed apophyses. Scutellum hardly visible. Metanotum not hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, unsculptured, with posterior surface strongly transversely striate. Mesopleuron and metapleuron transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture obsolete in 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCDFE4348A7537EFF59FB9A" box="[151,252,1106,1130]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">holotype</typeStatus>
, with anterior third very slightly visible in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18FCDFE434B9F537EFC50FB9A" box="[943,1013,1106,1130]" name="China" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">China</collectingCountry>
, Daheba. Segment 1 of protarsus of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCDFE4348A7535AFF5CFB7E" box="[151,249,1142,1166]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">holotype</typeStatus>
as long as segment 4. Protarsal segments of specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18FCDFE434BF1535AFBA2FB7E" box="[961,1031,1142,1166]" name="China" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">China</collectingCountry>
, Daheba, in following proportions: 15:3:5:18:27. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCDFE4349C653B6FDDDFB42" box="[502,632,1178,1202]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">Plate 120C</figureCitation>
) with one large subdistal tooth and one row of eight-ten lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCDFE4349845392FD96FB26" box="[436,563,1214,1238]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">Plate 120C</figureCitation>
) with two rows of 15 lamellae; distal apex with at least 16 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FCDFE4348F7522BFE2BFAEE" blockId="387.[150,1437,854,1598]" box="[199,398,1286,1311]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FCDFE4348F7522BFEAEFAEF" bold="true" box="[199,267,1287,1311]" pageId="387" pageNumber="388">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
